  - Rust
  - Python
  - R
  - WebAssembly
abstract: >-
  A linter for LaTeX / Sweave / R Markdown manuscripts submitted to the
  Journal of Statistical Software (JSS). One rule engine, shipped as a
  Python package, a Rust CLI, a browser/npm WebAssembly build, a native
  Python extension, an R package, a zero-install VS Code extension, and a
  GitHub Action — with byte-identical output across engines, and per-rule
  precision measured empirically against a pinned corpus of real JSS
  manuscripts.
